Donald]]></category><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F4c57aa90-b88c-11ee-9bfb-526531cc4a21&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=4910986e33aa35863fbe3e86638cba19ac0facd3" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F4c57aa90-b88c-11ee-9bfb-526531cc4a21&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=eb804acf90793f23a46f933b46abca1485c06d78" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Amazon 2023 Echo Show 8]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[2023 Echo Show 8]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[NASA says it’s reestablished contact with the Ingenuity Mars helicopter]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>经过短暂的令人担忧的沉默后， <a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:1;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://x.com/NASAJPL/status/1748883252604236281?s=20" data-original-link="https://x.com/NASAJPL/status/1748883252604236281?s=20">美国宇航局</a>周六晚表示，它能够与“聪明号”直升机重新取得联系。周四，这架自主飞机在火星上进行第 72 次飞行时意外停止了与“毅力”号火星车的通信，该火星车负责中继“独创”号和地球之间的所有传输。在此之前它就已经出现了问题，由于未知原因缩短了之前的飞行时间，美国宇航局打算在最近一次上升期间进行系统检查。 </p><div id="7b771133bf58428283ee4366e3057cc2"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">今天的好消息：在指示<a href="https://twitter.com/NASAPersevere?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@NASAPersevere</a>对 Ingenuity 的信号进行长时间监听后，我们已与<a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/MarsHelicopter?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#MarsHelicopter</a>重新建立了联系。<br><br>该团队正在审查新数据，以更好地了解 72 号航班期间意外的通讯中断<a href="https://t.co/KvCVwhZ5Rk">。https://t.co/KvCVwhZ5Rk</a></p> — NASA JPL (@NASAJPL) <a href="https://twitter.com/NASAJPL/status/1748883252604236281?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2024 年 1 月 21 日</a></blockquote></div><p>该航天局在 X 上发布的更新中表示，它现在正在审查来自 Ingenuity 的数据，以了解发生了什么。在团队指示“毅力”进行“长时间聆听会话”后，“毅力”号接收到了信号。聪明号之前曾经历过停电，最近一次是在去年，但后来又恢复飞行。但现在判断这次是否会出现这种情况还为时过早。这架迷你直升机的运行时间已经远远超过了最初的任务时间表。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/nasa-says-its-rebuilted-contact-with-the-ingenuity-mars-helicopter-165728606.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/nasa-says-its-reestablished-contact-with-the-ingenuity-mars-helicopter-165728606.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 59cac79c-9389-44f5-ba05-fac6ddf7f25a </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cheyenne MacDonald]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Sun, 21 Jan 2024 16:57:28 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1705856250</ingested><modified> 2024-01-21T16:57:33+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Cheyenne MacDonald]]></category><media:content height="1042" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2Fa42205e0-b87d-11ee-bff6-7499342c94f6&amp;resize=1400%2C1042&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=c78855699474c5ba2aa5bf59dd1755ea61573a5a" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1042" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2Fa42205e0-b87d-11ee-bff6-7499342c94f6&amp;resize=1400%2C1042&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=73221f3e4126779d143a8ac07b07c62ac41078eb" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NASA/JPL-Caltech/ASU/MSSS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[NASA's Ingenuity helicopter on the surface of Mars]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Ingenuity on Mars]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[NASA’s Ingenuity helicopter has gone silent on Mars]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>美国国家航空航天局（NASA）在本周早些时候与“独创”号火星直升机失去联系后，正在试图弄清楚如何到达该直升机。 <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://mars.nasa.gov/technology/helicopter/status/508/flight-72-status-update/">NASA</a>表示，在第 72 次飞行期间（“快速弹出”到约 40 英尺的高度），“聪明号”在与“毅力”号火星车应有的通信之前就停止了通信。周四一切归于平静，截至周五下午，NASA 仍未收到任何消息。</p><p>毅力号是直升机所有通讯的中间人；聪明号将信息发送给毅力号，然后毅力号将信息传递给地球，反之亦然。据美国宇航局称，这架小型直升机按计划完成了上升，但在返回途中停止了通信。美国宇航局在周五的状态更新中表示：“独创号团队正在分析可用数据，并考虑下一步与直升机重新建立通信。”聪明号此前曾提前结束了一次飞行，周四的短途旅行旨在“检查直升机的系统”。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>自 2021 年“独创号”随毅力号火星车抵达这颗红色星球以来，它就一直在这颗红色星球上。它远远超出了其任务目标。美国宇航局最初希望这架实验直升机能够完成几次飞行。它在运营的第一年里就连续飞行了 20 多次。该航天局于 2022 年正式延长其任务期限，此后又执行了数十次成功的飞行。 Ingenuity是第一架从火星表面起飞的飞机。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/nasas-ingenuity-helicopter-has-gone-silent-on-mars-195746735.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/nasas-ingenuity-helicopter-has-gone-silent-on-mars-195746735.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 589eba1e-c911-4e6e-b67c-dcc84e09e017 </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cheyenne MacDonald]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Sat, 20 Jan 2024 19:57:46 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1705781927</ingested><modified> 2024-01-20T20:18:51+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[Space & Astronomy]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Cheyenne MacDonald]]></category><media:content height="820" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F8b3546c0-b7cc-11ee-adef-a70258c325e7&amp;resize=1400%2C820&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=7a141f32f3da6cc089ea9cb2492ea408f161520f" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="820" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F8b3546c0-b7cc-11ee-adef-a70258c325e7&amp;resize=1400%2C820&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=a0f94c898800ab5b2aa14b7619ef1a43220da237" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NASA/JPL-Caltech/ASU/MSSS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The Ingenuity helicopter in an image taken by the Perseverance rover]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[NASA Ingenuity Mars helicopter]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Take a look at the full asteroid Bennu sample in all its glory]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>谁不喜欢炫耀他们收藏的酷炫岩石？经过几个月的努力，美国宇航局上周<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:1;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/nasa-finally-got-the-stuck-lid-off-its-asteroid-bennu-sample-container-185814782.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/nasa-finally-got-the-stuck-lid-off-its-asteroid-bennu-sample-container-185814782.html"><ins>终于能够进入小行星贝努样本容器</ins></a>，现在，它正在分享里面的情况。美国宇航局周五发布了新启用的“一触即走”样本采集机制（TAGSAM）的高分辨率图像，揭示了奥西里斯-雷克斯从小行星表面刮下的所有尘埃和岩石。</p><p>图像很大，因此您可以放大以查看样本的更精细细节。在<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:2;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/orex-high-res.jpg" data-original-link="https://www.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/orex-high-res.jpg"><ins>NASA 网站</ins></a>上查看全尺寸版本。科学家们可以利用的材料非常丰富，正如 OSIRIS-REx 团队成员<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:3;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://blogs.nasa.gov/osiris-rex/2023/09/29/initial-curation-of-nasas-osiris-rex-sample/" data-original-link="https://blogs.nasa.gov/osiris-rex/2023/09/29/initial-curation-of-nasas-osiris-rex-sample/"><ins>Lindsay Keller</ins></a>在 9 月份所说，他们计划充分利用微分析技术来“真正将其分解，几乎达到原子尺度”。据估计，小行星贝努 (Bennu) 的年龄约为 45 亿年，它可能蕴藏着有关太阳系形成以及生命的组成部分如何首次来到地球的线索。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>科学家们已经在 TAGSAM 外部发现的多余材料中发现了碳和水的迹象。虽然他们希望从小行星上获取至少 2.1 盎司（60 克）的风化层，但 OSIRIS-REx 却能够获取更多。该团队仅从样品硬件上积累的“奖励”材料中获得了 2.48 盎司（70.3 克）。美国宇航局计划在未来两年内分析部分样本，但其中大部分将被保存以供未来研究并与其他科学家共享。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/take-a-look-at-the-full-asteroid-bennu-sample-in-all-its-glory-161309568.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/take-a-look-at-the-full-asteroid-bennu-sample-in-all-its-glory-161309568.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 77b72294-644e-49cc-94da-1de2593ab521 </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cheyenne MacDonald]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Sat, 20 Jan 2024 16:13:09 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1705767191</ingested><modified> 2024-01-20T16:13:16+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Cheyenne MacDonald]]></category><media:content height="1050" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F823ff980-b7ad-11ee-bffc-4efc582a7c2e&amp;resize=1400%2C1050&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=3fdaf3a8919b447d4ad10d5491697d02a9b94475" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1050" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F823ff980-b7ad-11ee-bffc-4efc582a7c2e&amp;resize=1400%2C1050&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=e59fafc304ab7be3877894d45fe9f9987a3464d2" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NASA/Erika Blumenfeld/Joseph Aebersold]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A top-down look into the sample container showing dark dust and rocks taken from asteroid Bennu]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Asteroid Bennu sample]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Morning After: Apple's Vision Pro is almost here and Samsung's AI gambit]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>欢迎回到周六早上的科技注射。本周的 TMA 重点关注两项大型科技发布。首先，三星凭借其旗舰智能手机系列提前开启了2024年，宣布三款S24机型将于月底上市。当然，这一次它们看起来又像去年的手机了，但这被一系列其他智能手机上找不到的人工智能技巧和功能所抵消。这不就是买一部新手机的意义吗？</p><p>随着 Vision Pro（3,500 美元）在本月晚些时候推出之前开始预购，我们对苹果首次涉足 VR/AR/XR 领域也有了更深入的印象。你的口袋很大吧？这是该公司自 2014 年 Apple Watch 推出以来的首款新产品，我们最近的印象表明 Vision Pro 是一种流畅、智能的耳机体验，超越了我们迄今为止见过的 VR 耳机。两名 Engadget 编辑佩戴 Vision Pro 进行了一些<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-vision-pro-hands-on-redux-immersive-video-disney-app-floating-keyboard-and-a-little-screaming-180006222.html">更广泛的演示</a>，包括沉浸式视频，并尝试在 Vision Pro 的浮动键盘上进行稀薄打字。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="f6bfbb8605c64fe48a7c308f5959dc6f"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/o8fHKOXI4UA?si=bZWSrbxiY_NS7OZ3" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div><p><strong>本星期：</strong></p><p> 🥽🍎 <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-vision-pro-hands-on-redux-immersive-video-disney-app-floating-keyboard-and-a-little-screaming-180006222.html">Apple Vision Pro 上手、redux</a></p><p> 🕹️R🕹️R <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/take-twos-lawyers-think-remedys-new-r-logo-is-too-similar-to-rockstars-r-logo-181534083.html">Take-Two 的律师认为 Remedy 的新 R 标志与 Rockstar 的 R 标志太相似</a></p><p>📱📲 <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s24-ultra-hands-on-a-fresh-titanium-frame-combined-with-a-big-bet-on-ai-180050005.html">三星 Galaxy S24 Ultra 上手体验：</a></p><p></p><p><strong>读这个：</strong></p><p>谢丽尔·桑德伯格 (Sheryl Sandberg) 即将<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sheryl-sandberg-is-leaving-metas-board-003630253.html">离开</a>Meta 的董事会，公司继续向 Metaverse 航行，而我们其他人则想知道这是否是一个存在的目的地。该公司还在重组其人工智能团队。该公司有两个团队致力于人工智能研究，但现在马克·扎克伯格正在让他们更加紧密地联系在一起。这会导致什么？卡丽莎·贝尔<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/mark-zuckerberg-is-the-latest-billionaire-who-wants-to-create-artificial-general-intelligence-210820789.html">解释了这一切</a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-apples-vision-pro-is-almost-here-and-samsungs-ai-gambit-150028059.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-apples-vision-pro-is-almost-here-and-samsungs-ai-gambit-150028059.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 3b475022-2222-4d3a-b905-3eac18d694f8 </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mat Smith]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Sat, 20 Jan 2024 15:00:28 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1705677123</ingested><modified> 2024-01-19T15:12:12+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mat Smith]]></category><media:content height="787" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F21ab7850-b6dc-11ee-aaff-917ae6986daf&amp;resize=1400%2C787&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=17db3e0e5ab68846bbabbe6d0074bb2f0a9388af" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="787" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F21ab7850-b6dc-11ee-aaff-917ae6986daf&amp;resize=1400%2C787&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=929c111045e85f1dab5e3573f52301eee5425cbc" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[TMA]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[TMA]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Apple Vision Pro repairs could set you back as much as $2,399]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>如果您打算购买<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-vision-pro-hands-on-redux-immersive-video-disney-app-floating-keyboard-and-a-little-screaming-180006222.html">Apple Vision Pro</a> ，您可能还想购买一个保护壳。根据<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://appleinsider.com/articles/24/01/19/damaged-apple-vision-pro-repairs-cost-up-to-2399"><em>AppleInsider</em></a>首次注意到的该公司的设备<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N1cHBvcnQuYXBwbGUuY29tL2FwcGxlLXZpc2lvbi1wcm8vcmVwYWlyIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI0Y2ZkMGViZS1iNjJhLTQ3NTAtODA4Ny1kYzYzZjYzYjVmMGMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAfhR0btseTerS7d1DEQNM1N1uh4QhbaD1LU3sRhDjBn0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.apple.com%2Fapple-vision-pro%2Frepair" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://support.apple.com/apple-vision-pro/repair">维修和服务页面</a>，即使您有 AppleCare+，维修费用也可能非常昂贵。如果耳机的玻璃盖破裂，您需要花费 799 美元进行更换。其他类型的损坏可能会让您损失高达 2,399 美元，仅比全新基本单元便宜 1,100 美元。</p><p>如果你购买 AppleCare+，维修价格听起来并没有那么离谱，但仍然不便宜。损坏的保修或任何其他类型的维修将花费您 299 美元，此外还有每月 25 美元的延长保修费。虽然您可以由第三方修复它，但如果您将来将其发送给 Apple 进行另一次维修，则可能会导致问题，而这些服务可能没有您需要的组件。不过，苹果公司最近一直<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-backs-right-to-repair-bill-in-california-072227964.html?_fsig=fiZ4IjsjB0tIV_nNZEO0aw--%7EA">支持维修权</a>运动，并为其手机和电脑制定了<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apples-expanded-self-repair-program-covers-the-iphone-14-and-newer-macbooks-193435980.html">现有的自我维修计划</a>。该公司可以将 Vision Pro 添加到该计划中，但这可能不会很快发生。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Apple Vision Pro 现已<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-vision-pro-pre-orders-are-now-open-130056024.html">可在 Apple 美国网站和全国所有实体店预订</a>。 3,499 美元的版本将为您提供 256GB 的存储空间，而 512GB 的版本将为您提供 3,699 美元。想要 1TB 空间吗？这笔费用为 3,899 美元。请注意，其配件是单独出售的，您需要额外支付 199 美元购买旅行箱。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/apple-vision-pro-repairs-could-set-you-back-as-much-as-2399-141439566.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/apple-vision-pro-repairs-could-set-you-back-as-much-as-2399-141439566.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 4cfd0ebe-b62a-4750-8087-dc63f63b5f0c</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mariella Moon]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Sat, 20 Jan 2024 14:14:39 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1705768531</ingested><modified> 2024-01-20T16:35:35+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="903" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F9dc3b3e0-b771-11ee-9fd9-06654cd07df1&amp;resize=1400%2C903&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=26a03ab4396b348f82534140eb818b52b1afbea4" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit